attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi there from brothers Sam and Bobby! Sam here - I am the handsome orange guy; my brother, Bobby, isn't bad looking, either, with those cool tiger stripes and that come hither look.  We are pretty laid back and are currently interviewing humans for our next home. (We would really prefer not to be near noisy machines here like the "washing machine", whatever THAT is.) We just turned 3-years-old in May - Happy Birthday to us! The best gift would be to have a place we can call home. We think we're kind of perfect. We haven't been with other cats or dogs so we'd probably have to figure that out together. In this great country, everyone should have a cat - or two!

If you're interested in Sam and Bobby, stop by the shelter during our adoption hours: Tuesdays & Thursdays from 6-8pm and Saturdays from 10am-4pm or email our Feline Manager at felinemanager@quincyanimalshelter.org

attributes.descriptionHtml:
You can call me casanova because I am a LOVER! I love to give kisses and snuggle nice and close. I love dinnertime.  I play very well with other dogs. I would love to be a part of your family!

Bernie is 9 months old- a bulldog/ beagle mix. UTD on vaccinations and neutered- His adoption fee is $250.00.

Name: Beabull
Mix: 1/2 Beagle x 1/2 Bulldog
Mixes: More Beagle Mixes , More Bulldog Mixes






Appearance: Beabulls have the Bulldog wrinkles and underbite.


Characteristics: Beabulls are amazing jumpers.


Personality: Beabulls are extremely friendly and always willing to give kisses and cuddle.


Temperament: Beabulls are loveable, even-tempered, easy going, non-aggressive dogs. Beabulls can be very hyper while they are playing.


Family Dog: Beabulls make good family dogs. They love little children and don't seem to mind when they cry or scream. Small children should be supervised when playing with a Beabull. Beabulls are mellow dogs, but get excited while playing and may lightly play-bite.


Ears: The ears of a Beabull are not quite as big as a full blooded beagle, but have the same style.


Muzzle: Beabulls have very strong jaws.


Body: Beabulls have a very strong, sleak body like a Beagle with hips like a Bulldog.


Feet: Beabulls have feet similiar to a bulldog.


Tail: The Beabulls tail may be docked.


Color: Beabulls have a mixture of Beagle and Bulldog coloring.





Coat: Beabulls have a softer coat on her sides with coarse, prickly coat on the top of their back.


Shedding: Beabulls shed a lot.


Training: Beabulls respond fairly well to commands and are very easy to potty train.


Behavior: Beabulls love to play like a Beagle but have sluggish Bulldog moments. Beabulls love to cuddle and be close to people. Beabulls are vigorous chewers and can destroy their toys. Beabulls have the beagle obsession with sniffing things.


Barking: Beabulls bark occasionally, especially when people come to the door.


Weather: Beabulls love to spend time outside in the summer and warm weather. In the winter they may enjoy a romp in the snow and chasing snowballs.


Exercise: Beabulls can be pretty lazy, but do love to chew and play tug-o-war.


Physical Ability: Beabulls are amazing jumpers.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Adoption Pending 

Filling out an  application from our web site at www.caninecastaways.org  is the first step in adopting a new furry family member.

NAME:   Tippy
BREED:  Shih Tzu/Dachshund mix
SEX:  female
COLOR:  brown/tan/white
AGE:  Born March 1, 2016
WEIGHT:  5 lbs as of May 9, 2016

 

FOSTERED BY:   Timea
LOCATED IN:  Sarasota


NOTES FROM FOSTER FAMILY:

Tippy and her brother Tony are puppies that were born in our care.  After we rescued their mother Annie (who is a Shih Tzu) we realized she was far along in a pregnancy and going to be giving birth soon.  They are the only 2 from the litter and love each other.  They would love to get a home together but could be separated as long as they go to homes that have at least one other dog that is going to play with them and allow them to be "puppies" and jump, play, etc. with them.

They are working on potty training and getting used to normal "life" noises.  They are both very sweet and happy.

Local adoptions only - Manatee, Sarasota, Charlotte, Lee, Collier counties.  These puppies will need to be brought back to our vet in Arcadia for follow up vaccines as well as spay/neuter surgery when they are old enough.  

If you are interested in adopting please Complete our Adoption Application by copying and pasting the following link into your web browser: http://www.caninecastaways.org/#!adopt/c6mv


MEDICAL INFO:


The following has been or will be done for this puppy at the appropriate age...
- Basic Exam by Veterinarian
- Spayed or Neutered
- Placed on heartworm preventive
- Basic Bloodwork
- Microchipped
- Intestinal Parasite Exam and medication
- Vaccinations
- Placed on flea preventive


ADOPTION DONATION: $300


This adoption donation helps to cover the vet expenses for this puppy including heartworm preventive which is dispensed at the initial vet visit and then goes with the dog at adoption. All vet records will be provided to adopter.

Visit us at www.caninecastaways.org

attributes.descriptionHtml:
RESCUED FROM A HIGH KILL SHELTER, NOW IN NEED OF A HOME!

COCO is a VERY CUTE, adorable 9 month old, 25 lb, chocolate terrier mix pup who was saved from a high kill shelter, where she and her litter mates had been turned in. She is a wonderful 'cinnamony' color, with unique grey hair effects on her back above the below chocolate coloring. A docile, gentle, playful, sweet, fun loving girl, who is eager to please and responds terrifically to praise and kindness. Coco loves to give kisses! Coco gets along terrifically with other dogs, even large ones. Coco is spayed, current on vaccinations, house-trained and crate-trained. Contact: 215-450-8335
Coco is presently residing in the Rootstown Ohio area.

Coco is not a Rose's Rescue dog. Please contact Coco's caregiver at 215-450-8335.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
2016/05/22

Danny has been a very popular dog and we are no longer accepting applications. Please consider another of our deserving dogs!

Adoption Fee Applies

Name/Tag#: Danny 3354

Age: 1.5 years

Sex/Altered: Male/ Neutered

Weight: 16lbs

Breed: Schnauzer

Foster Home Location: OSHAWA, ON

Adoption Fee: $500.00

Temperament: Loving, friendly, slightly nervous

Activity/Energy Level: Medium, loves to chase a ball

Up to date on Shots: Yes

Housebroken: Yes

Crate Trained: Yes

Ok with Dogs: Yes

Ok with Cats: Unknown

Ok with Kids: Yes, over 8 years old please

Origin: Owner surrender

Requirements: Securely fenced yard, someone home most of the day, experienced dog owner, detached home


And now, a few words from me:

Hi, my name is Danny and I'm looking for a forever home. I'm staying in my foster home but don't know how long I will be here - perhaps you could tell me? My foster mom and dad say they don't expect me to be here long as they think I am a good boy who will be a popular dog. I hope so, even though it is fun here. I have a dog friend to play with and we have become great
friends.

And now, a few words from my foster mom:

Danny is a lovely boy. Although he is only 1.5 years old, he can be a calm dog to have around but he does get anxious if he thinks you are leaving the house. He has brought new life into our 9 year old dog who has been playing with him ever since he got here and I think he has exhausted poor Danny. Danny eats well, is house trained, sleeps in his crate and only gets up when
you get up, is well mannered and knows lie, sit and stay. He 'bongs" around the yard as he jumps when he runs - so cute to watch. Danny might do well in agility classes. As he is still a puppy, he is mouthy when playing with you but he does this
gently. He takes treats gently, patiently waiting his turn. He likes squeaky toys and will drop a toy at your feet to say "come and play".

He goes into the yard to do his business but likes to come right back in unless you stay with him, however, knowing 'stay' he is increasing his time left outside. Danny has been a very popular dog and we are no longer accepting applications. Please consider another of our deserving dogs!

Adoption Fee Applies

Age: 1.5 years

Sex/Altered: Male/ Neutered

Weight: 16lbs

Breed: Schnauzer

Foster Home Location: OSHAWA, ON

Adoption Fee: $500.00

Temperament: Loving, friendly, slightly nervous

Activity/Energy Level: Medium, loves to chase a ball

Up to date on Shots: Yes

Housebroken: Yes

Crate Trained: Yes

Ok with Dogs: Yes

Ok with Cats: Unknown

Ok with Kids: Yes, over 8 years old please

Origin: Owner surrender

Requirements: Securely fenced yard, someone home most of the day, experienced dog owner, detached home


And now, a few words from me:

Hi, my name is Danny and I'm looking for a forever home. I'm staying in my foster home but don't know how long I will be here - perhaps you could tell me? My foster mom and dad say they don't expect me to be here long as they think I am a good boy who will be a popular dog. I hope so, even though it is fun here. I have a dog friend to play with and we have become great
friends.

And now, a few words from my foster mom:

Danny is a lovely boy. Although he is only 1.5 years old, he can be a calm dog to have around but he does get anxious if he thinks you are leaving the house. He has brought new life into our 9 year old dog who has been playing with him ever since he got here and I think he has exhausted poor Danny. Danny eats well, is house trained, sleeps in his crate and only gets up when
you get up, is well mannered and knows lie, sit and stay. He 'bongs" around the yard as he jumps when he runs - so cute to watch. Danny might do well in agility classes. As he is still a puppy, he is mouthy when playing with you but he does this
gently. He takes treats gently, patiently waiting his turn. He likes squeaky toys and will drop a toy at your feet to say "come and play".

He goes into the yard to do his business but likes to come right back in unless you stay with him, however, knowing 'stay' he is increasing his time left outside. Someone around in the day would be good. He barks when someone comes to the door so not good for an apartment. We like having Danny around but not sure he will he be here that long? What do you think?
Fill in an application to see what a great companion he is.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Dog Name: Domino
Suspected Breed(s): Chihuahua mix
Gender: Male
Age: 2 yrs old
Weight: ~15 lbs
Personality: Friendly, Curious, Patient, Smart, Easygoing, Outgoing, Loyal, Quick Learner, Loyal, Friendly, Adaptable, Gentle, Quiet, Funny, Affectionate, Shy, Playful, Snuggler, Calm, Trainable
Observations with Dogs: Adores dogs! Has tons of fun with the two resident dogs in his foster home.
Observations with Cats: Good with cats. Mostly ignores, but he and one of the resident cats in his foster home occasionally play. 
Observations with Kids: Loves kids. Domino is very gentle. Gets along really well with the 3 year old in his foster home.
House Training Progress: Occasional accidents
Crate Training Progress: Great in the crate! 
Location: DC area foster
Rescued From: Roane County, WV
Additional Information: Domino is a keeper! He is also affectionately known as “Chip” or “Chipper.” Domino is loveable to humans, dogs, and cats of all ages. He jumps and wiggles his body gleefully when it's time to go outside, topping it off with a little dance on his hind legs. He will sit on your lap, or sit next to you. He will sleep under your covers, or at the foot of the bed. Domino does not insist on coming up on the furniture to be a lap dog, but will do so when invited. Domino is a wonderful companion to humans and dogs. He is perfect if you are looking for a friend for an existing dog(s), and will be your faithful companion if you are alone. Never mind the cats; he will go with their flow! He's not a yapper, and if he does bark out the window, he will quiet down when asked. Apply today to bring Domino home!

 

If you are interested in meeting a dog, we require an adoption application. Visit http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/adopt.html to apply. If a dog has "HAS APPLICATION" listed, they are still available to receive additional applications but also may be in the process of being adopted soon.

 

If a dog has "NEEDS FOSTER" listed, they are still available for adoption. Information about our current dogs in need of fosters can be found here: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/current-dogs-in-need-of-a-foster.html and the application to foster is here: http://www.citydogsrescuedc.org/foster.html.

 

City Dogs Rescue is a foster based rescue in Washington, DC. We do not have a shelter. We focus on local adoptions in DC and the metro area of Maryland and Virginia. CDR has a thorough adoption process in order to find the best possible fit for each of our dogs (we do not operate under a first-come, first-served model).

 

Prior to arrival, all of our dogs are spayed/neutered (unless specified) and given shots for Rabies, Distemper DHPP, and Bordatella. They are tested for Heartworm, Lyme, Anaplasma, and Ehrlichia. They are dewormed at least twice and given a health check by the vet.  Most dogs will have a house training accident in the initial days in their new home and we cannot guarantee any dog is housebroken or crate trained. Our adoption fee is $395 (including puppies) unless noted -- senior dogs are available for an adoption fee of $200.

 

We also update our Facebook page daily with new dogs.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Herb, the many-toed cat!  The cat with ginormous paws!  Herb is a cat like you’ve never met before.  He loves to play fetch, is super affectionate, has a purr that will wake you up in the morning, and…did I mention those paws?  He loves to climb high places, look out the window to see the goings-on, lie in the sun, and groom those gigantic paws.  He is tall and lean and long, and he has beautiful eyes as well. 

One of Herb’s favorite activities is fetching plastic shower rings.  You throw, he fetches and brings it back to you. Endless amusement!  Of course he loves all other kinds of cat toys – feathers, laser dots, cat dancers, foil balls, catnip!  He uses the cardboard scratching post like a champ. I have never seen him scratch furniture.  In the morning when he hears you stirring, he will come in, sit on your chest, and purr, purr, purr while you pet him.  It’s quite a lovely way to start the day.

Herb likes to eat, so you better be ready with his food at mealtime or he’ll let you know to step on it!  He currently lives in a house with two small dogs and several cats.   He gets along fine with all them and sometimes naps with one of the cats. 

One thing about all those toes, you will need to be comfortable clipping his nails because the extra one will become ingrown and will require a vet visit if you don’t.  Fortunately, Herb is very good natured and will allow you to clip his claws.

Meet Sparkle... she is a sweet adorable little girl. she got her name from the sparkles in her eyes when she see you coming! She is very loving, and still has puppy energy. Time to move on I suppose. Here’s a little bit about me; first and foremost, I am adorable…  I’m just going to throw that out there right now. Secondly, I LOVE to play. attributes.descriptionHtml:
Bentley's owner got him from a family member but was allergic and couldn't keep him so he brought him to YWAC on April 19 and surrendered him for adoption.  Bentley is about 4 years old.  He is front declawed and blind in both eyes.  He needs a quiet home where things stay the same and he can find his way around.  Bentley is fearful at first but if spoken to quietly and given time to become familiar with your voice and know that he can trust you, he is quite friendly and once he gains trust he loves to snuggle. He has to get used to your voice and he'll love you forever. He's shy at first but once he warms up to you he loves giving head bumps and kisses.

 

All Cat YWAC Adoptions Include: spay/neuter before leaving our facility, they receive an annual RCP combo vaccination (except Rabies), de-worming medication, Revolution flea treatment, a FeLV/FIV combo test and a microchip!! attributes.descriptionHtml:
Titan is a 1-year-old, 50-lb. Lab-mix boy who desperately needs to find a new home due to allergies in his family. He's super-friendly, loves kids and dogs, and — in classic retriever fashion — walks with a toy in his mouth everywhere he goes :-) Titan loves to play and snuggle with his family, and is thrilled when it's time to visit the dog park. He is housetrained, crate-trained, neutered, and up to date on all vaccinations.

Want to learn more? Please stop by an upcoming Meet & Greet to find out if Titan is the right pup for you! (Local adoptions preferred — Philadelphia and tri-state area [South Jersey and northern Delaware] only.)

PLEASE READ BEFORE CONTACTING US!  We are NOT a shelter: All of our dogs live in private homes with foster families. Come and meet the Almost Home dogs and their fosters at our Meet & Greet events, where you can learn more about our wonderful dogs from the people who live with them, find out which dogs are on their way and when they’ll arrive, and fill out an application to adopt or foster.

We cannot adopt to homes where electric-shock fencing systems or training collars are used. For more information on the dangers of electric-shock collars, please visit  banshockcollars.ca/studies.php and http://www.hollysden.com/say_no_to_shock.htm (scroll down and click on the  "Invisible Fencing Systems" link).

We do not have an online adoption application; to request an application, e-mail us at  AlmostHome4Dogs@yahoo.com . To speed e-mail processing time, be sure to note the name of the dog you are inquiring about in the Subject line. For Meet & Greet times and locations, visit our home page, where you also will find information on our adoption process and fees.

FOSTER FAMILIES ARE LIFESAVERS!! Can you open your heart and home for a few weeks to homeless shelter dog? Remember, by fostering a dog, you save TWO lives — that of your foster dog, and that of the dog who takes his place in the shelter! Come to a Meet & Greet and find out if fostering is for you — there's no reward quite like the feeling that you've saved a life ... or two!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Jewels is a beautiful girl that loves to explore and play. She needs to see everything that you are doing, she is our explorer. She plays very well with all of the other dogs and really enjoys her toys. She is potty pad trained and crate trained. She would love to sleep with you if you allow it, but remember that she is a puppy and may have an accident in your bedroom. She likes to chase balls, but won’t bring it back to you yet. Jewels loves her Hooves to chew on and helps her with her teething. We recommend that you have them in your home, only one of them will last for weeks. She is not leashed trained yet, so you will have to work on that. Jewels doesn’t mind cats but she is curious and will sniff them. Jewels is very smart and catches on quickly, so training hasn’t been too hard. Remember that she is a puppy and will still need more training, but she would make a great addition to any family that likes to be active.

SECURE FENCING REQUIRED FOR ALL OF OUR RESCUED DOGS.

If you are considering adopting a dog through HALO Here are some helpful hints:

Bring pictures of your yard to show secure fencing. Most of our dogs require a 6 foot fenced yard. Yards must be cleared of any fox tail weeds.

We do adopt small dogs to apartments or condo and need to see pictures of the patio or balcony area. If you rent, please bring copy of your lease to show you can have pets and any size restrictions.

We do not adopt to homes with children under the age of five unless we know the history of the dog with young children. All Children MUST be present at adoption.

If you own a dog and are looking for a friend please bring your dog with you so they can be introduced.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Introducing Garrett. He is a 2 year old male Poodle/Bichon Frise mix. He currently weighs 15 lbs. Garrett gets along well with other dogs, and will make a great lap dog. He will do best in a home with children over the age of 12.

Garrett's foster mother had this to say about him:

"I have had Garrett for about 4 days and he's a little slow to warm up, but then will be your shadow.   He seems to warm up to women faster than men, met our grandson, age 14 and was great.  Garrett loves my dogs and will chase them around the backyard.  Also, he met the dog next door, a large pit mix female, just fell in with our dogs chasing her up and down the fence line. The only time I have had an issue with him is after he was settled in our home and my other dogs wanted to sit on my lap.  He went towards them with a little growl, but never tried to bite. After I moved him off my lap and told him no, I picked up my dog and made Garrett stay on the floor.  That seemed to hurt his feelings and he rolled over for a belly rub (which of course he got!), but on the floor.  He is making some progress with the jealousy issue - it's not really that bad.  I think he just was glad he had someone to give him some attention and wasn't going to give it up.  He and my husband are good friends now, except it scared him when my husband was carrying a load of towels downstairs - I think big unknown things scare him.  Like most dogs, Garrett barked at the lawn mower but after a minute or so, was ok with the vacuum.  He tends to play hard, so small children would not be suitable in a home with Garrett. He did pee the first few days in the house but,  after he got the schedule down and started going out with my dogs he's been fine.  He hasn't chewed on anything, but did try to pick up a shoe and a flip flop but dropped them after I told him no.  I have left him alone for 3-4 hrs with my dogs and he has been fine - he loves fuzzy toys."

His minimum adoption donation is $295 plus a $10 fee for rabies registration with McLean County Animal Control (McLean County residents).

He has been neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm and fecal checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.

For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm

To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Ruby is a beautiful little girl that just wants to be loved on. She is the mellower one of the two puppies that we have. She loves to play with her sister Jewels and the other dogs that are gentle. She is potty pad trained and crate trained. Ruby really enjoys playing in the yard with the other dogs. She is curious about the cats and will sniff them, other than that she doesn't bother the cats in the house. This little girl love to snuggle and will bury her head into your neck. She loves to have her belly rubbed. Ruby loves her Hooves to chew on and it helps her with her teething. We recommend that you have them in your home, only one of them will last for weeks. She is not leashed trained yet, so you will have to work on that. She would make a wonderful addition to any family without children 6 years of age or under.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hunter is a 32 lb. Lab/Pointer mix that is approximately 3 years old.   He was brought in as a stray to the Hope Vet Clinic from a Good Samaritan as a farmer wanted to shoot him.   He is a total GEM!!   He is submissive to other pets, but pretty much just leaves them alone.   He is very quiet (hasn’t barked yet) and shy, but does like affection.  He also loves a soft bed.  He has found all the soft places to lay at the foster’s house.   He is crate and potty trained and on walks he does not pull, but does need some more leash training.   Hunter also seems to be ok with cats…he has stared at them, but didn’t chase them.   Hunter is VERY gentle and mild.   He hasn’t been around children that we are aware of, but we believe he would be great.    This sweet boy is looking for his forever home and the family who adopts Hunter would be lucky to have him.   If you are interested in meeting Hunter, please fill out an application.

She is a very active and playful girl. She needs a home that can provide her with the exercise and attention she needs. She's very smart, and will do well with training and would probably make a good agility dog!
Her minimum adoption donation is $295.
She has been spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, heartworm and fecal checked, dewormed, and is on flea and heartworm preventatives.
For information about this dog's breed(s), visit: http://www.dogbreedinfo.com/abc.htm
To fill out our adoption application, go to: http://fs16.formsite.com/WishBoneCanineRescue/adoptionapplication/index.html
attributes.name: Bell

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Introducing Dominic, a sweet, 1-2 year old Terrier mix, who traveled all the way from Puerto Rico to find his forever home.  Dominic is a gem!  He is super friendly and loves other dogs, as well as all people. Dominic has excellent house manners and is fully house trained.  He has a somewhat silly, eager to please personality that is sure to delight you. He is neutered, up-to-date on vaccines and preventatives and eager to find a family to love!

The adoption fee for this dog is $295, which includes routine vetting and spay/neuter. 

To complete an online application, please click here, then email Crystal at CWood@petconnectrescue.org.

attributes.descriptionHtml: SUPER SWEET & SPECIAL PUPPY:  9 months old / Currently 15 lbs.  Meet me Saturdays at 1 of our 2 Kennesaw locations from 11-4pm.  Check for my location at www.mostlymutts.org after 5pm on Fridays.  I'm a wonderful little puppy who's had a hard start to life, but I don't let anything get me down!  I came to Mostly Mutts with a spinal injury and 2 broken ribs, so I was unable to walk on my back legs at all.  Well, fast forward to now and I can walk and even run around having fun! I’m super friendly and affectionate with people and being held is one of my favorite pastimes. I love to lay in your lap!  I’m also all about PLAY!  I like to get all the toys out of the toy box and spread them all over the room and then zoom around pouncing and flipping into them. Playing ball outside is always fun for me too. I can be an only child or have a sweet and fun dog to play with in my new home as I love other dogs. I do not require lots of exercise, so you can sit back and watch me play or we can go for walks and play in the yard. I am very flexible. When you want me to be calm, just pick me up and I’ll fall fast asleep in your lap.  We are working on potty training.  I totally have the peeing part down and only go outside, but do to my injury I still poop sometimes when I start running around. It is really easy to clean up and I am doing better. I must stay slim to protect my back, so not too many treats for me please. I am learning to go upstairs with carpet, but I don’t even try to come down the stairs. The good thing is I am small enough to be picked up and carried up or down stairs. I'm good in my crate or puppy playpen and just a wonderful young pup! I am a very special puppy! Someone probably kicked me as a 6 week old puppy but now life is good and I can’t wait to find my new family. I will bring lots of laughter into the home. You can contact Tammy for more information about me at 770-314-8974.  My best friend is Izzy who also has a back issue, so if you happen to want 2 wonderful special needs doggies, MM's will let you adopt both of us for one adoption fee.  Energy level:  4 – 6.  I'm spayed, micro-chipped and current on my vaccinations.  My adoption fee is $275.00.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
AGE: about 11 weeks

ABOUT ME:  My name is Peanut.  I was found without a mom with my brother.  Lucky for us, TCPR took us in and we were took in by another mom cat and her kittens.   We had such fun spending the last few weeks with them but its time to find my own home!  I'm a sweet little girl.  I love playing and cuddling.  I love getting a treat of canned food for breakfast - it's the best part of waking up!   I get along with other cats.  I may be a little shy the first day or two, but will warm up when I know I'm safe and loved!   You should adopt me!

MORE ABOUT ME: I'm spayed/neutered, microchipped, and vaccinated appropriately for my age.  I tested negative for FIV/Felv. 

ADOPT ME: If you'd like to learn more about me or start the adoption process, please complete an Adoption Application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.tcpetrescue.org.

FOSTER ME: If you're interested in fostering me (or any other cat or dog), please complete a Foster Application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.tcpetrescue.org. If you have general questions about fostering cats, you may contact our volunteer cat coordinators at cats@tcpetrescue.org. If you have general questions about fostering dogs, you may contact our volunteer dog coordinators at dogs@tcpetrescue.org. Our rescue can only help as many animals for whom we have foster homes!

PLEASE NOTE: Twin Cities Pet Rescue does not adopt to homes farther than 60 miles from the Twin Cities metro area.

attributes.descriptionHtml: AN ACTIVE AND FUN GUY:  6 years old / 29 lbs.  I'm a fun-loving active dog who is looking for the same in my new home!  I lost my home because my owner didn't make time to meet my needs.  Although, I like napping on and off, I really love being active with my person.  I would love to have a running partner or someone who will take me places with them and have fun with me!  I'm really smart and know the commands 'sit', 'down', 'dance', 'stay', 'drop ball' and 'get ball'.  Speaking of balls, I'd enjoy a fenced yard if you have one so we could play ball together, but please don't leave me out unattended as I have gotten bored and dug out in my previous home.  In my foster home, I'm having fun with the other dog there.  We loves to wrestle, chase, and play tug of war together.  I was ganged up by a group of larger dogs at the dog park, so I can be defensive and snarly with larger dogs if I feel threatened.  Can you blame me?  I have great potty manners, am pretty good in a crate, but would rather sleep on a doggy bed at night instead of in the crate. I tuck myself in every night by tossing a blanket over myself and covering up snout to tail!  It's about the cutest thing you'll ever seen.  I whine a good bit when I'm bored, so let's make sure to be active together!  Keep a good hold on my lease and use caution with open doors as I get very happy when we're going places and may run off ahead and not know to come back.  My foster family is impressed with my good manners in the home and I think you will be too.  I'm good with kids and love playing with them, but best no toddlers as I'm energetic.  Energy level: 6 – 8.  I'm current on vaccinations, micro-chipped, neutered and my adoption fee is $195.00.  You can meet me Saturdays from 11:00 – 4pm at the Barrett Parkway / I-75 PetSmart.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
AGE: about 11 weeks

ABOUT ME:  My name is Peanut.  I was found without a mom with my brother.  Lucky for us, TCPR took us in and we were took in by another mom cat and her kittens.   We had such fun spending the last few weeks with them but its time to find my own home!  I'm a sweet little girl.  I love playing and cuddling.  I love getting a treat of canned food for breakfast - it's the best part of waking up!   I get along with other cats.  I may be a little shy the first day or two, but will warm up when I know I'm safe and loved!   You should adopt me!

MORE ABOUT ME: I'm spayed/neutered, microchipped, and vaccinated appropriately for my age.  I tested negative for FIV/Felv. 

ADOPT ME: If you'd like to learn more about me or start the adoption process, please complete an Adoption Application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.tcpetrescue.org.

FOSTER ME: If you're interested in fostering me (or any other cat or dog), please complete a Foster Application on the Twin Cities Pet Rescue website: www.tcpetrescue.org. If you have general questions about fostering cats, you may contact our volunteer cat coordinators at cats@tcpetrescue.org. If you have general questions about fostering dogs, you may contact our volunteer dog coordinators at dogs@tcpetrescue.org. Our rescue can only help as many animals for whom we have foster homes!

PLEASE NOTE: Twin Cities Pet Rescue does not adopt to homes farther than 60 miles from the Twin Cities metro area.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Stewie, aka Last Two Stories, is an almost 3-year-old brindle male born June 27. 2013. His sire is Pat C Clement and his dam is CJC's Punchie. Meet Miles- he is such a happy boy.... when he walks- he "prances". He is so sweet and loving.... even though when he was in the puppymill before he came to us- another dog chewed on his ears. Enoght so that one is half missing and the other is chewed around the tips.... it is so sad to think of that happening to him. Yet- he is so happy... he is just an amazing dog!

he is neutered, UTD on his vaccinations, heartworm tested and on preventative- and ready to go to a home with a lot of love to give him- becasue he has a lot to give back!
Miles is papertrained and does fine not being in a crate at all.
his adoption fee is $150.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
BENNEY is a delight. He came to Castaway Critters from a local vet office - he and his two brothers were dropped off during their first week of life. Shortly thereafter we placed these 3 siblings with a surrogate, lactating Momma cat who took excellent care of them (see Marie on our web site). Benny will be altered on Nov 11, 2008 and then will be ready for adoption. He is a well-adjusted kitten and loves to play and run around with his brothers.
If you are interested in Benny ( or two sweet boys, check out Regis' web site ) please contact Diane at kamp@comcast.net.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello there. I’m Sophie. Don’t you think the name suits me? I’m a very well behaved young lady whose owner decided they didn’t want me after all and they dumped me at a local shelter. Luckily enough I was bailed out in the nick of time! I’m a golden retriever/lab mix with pretty white feet. And I’m about 6 months old. My big brown eyes will make your heart melt.

I love to play ... with other dogs with balls! I know how to sit, to shake and down. I'm learning a few other commands too, and I'm a real fast learner. Since I'm a pup I like to rough house a little when I play, but don't be put off by that - I'm a gentle soul ... but I would like to be the alpha dog!

I would love to go home with you so you can get to know me. To know me is to love me!

posgted 10/20/08 tth

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Bubba is a gorgeous 2 year old Black and Tan Coonhound.  Bubba is good with kids and other dogs.  He is probably good with cats but we have not cat tested him yet. He rides nicely in the car and is very sweet and good natured.  He would love a home with a nice fenced-in yard and possibly another dog to hang out with.  Bubba is house and crate trained.

If you are interested in meeting Bubba, complete the  Adoption Application on our website at  www.NeedyPaws.org   and we will contact you.  Adopters will need to live within an hours drive of St. Louis, MO.

Bubba’s adoption fee is $250.00, which includes up-to-date vaccinations, heartworm testing and preventative, neuter  and microchip.

We are a 100% foster-based rescue and all of our dogs live in approved foster homes.  We are dedicated to finding the best Forever Homes and we will perform home visits and conduct veterinarian and reference checks for each potential adopter.
attributes.name: Bubba

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Beckett....he is a part of the "B" pups, what a gorgeous boy he is, and just as sweet as pie! He is very loving, and attentive. He has a great nature. He is good with his littermates. He is about 12 weeks old. This is a great litter of easy going puppies, of course they still have all those puppies kisses, and energy! They are up to date on vacc. and monthly preventions. VB  5/14/16

**It is rare that we know with certainty the ages or mixes that make up our wonderful dogs, but we do our best to be as accurate as possible based upon our many years in rescue.**


Adoption: $245  which covers quarantine, shots, worming, food, medical records and an Alabama State Health Certificate.  $35 of this fee is a Spay/Neuter deposit which will be returned to you upon receipt of proof  that the dog has been spayed or neutered.

Transport, if needed :  $120.00    We consider the transport to be of great importance and, as such, take particular care of the dogs during the trip from Alabama. We make every effort to arrive with healthy and minimally stressed dogs.

Hi! I'm a spunky gal named Dazzle and I am looking for my forever home. I was brought here with my sister Razzle and we get along pretty well, so I think I could make some new canine friends pretty easily in my new home. My favorite toy is a strong rope toy, and I love to play tug of war with my sister. I could teach a new friend to play too! I know I'm little for now, but I won't be for long, and will need some training as I get older .I'm looking for a family that might have the time to teach me new tricks and help me become the best pup I can be! If my blue eyes dazzle you, take me home today!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
My name is Tylie Mama Cat and I should have danced all night. I was a good mom and enjoyed raising those little guys but those babies are going to be my one and onlys. I’m a sweet, trusting girl. Hey, this is how I got in this situation!!! I’ll be looking for a family to love a hard working mama like me. I know there are a few of the two legged creatures in my same situation that can have a sympatric heart to take me in.

Here is what the crew has to say about me:
Tylie is slender and long of limb. She has huge golden eyes. She is a very beautiful cat. She has a affectionate personality too! She took great care of her babies and now she is looking for her own home. So how can you say no to a package like this!

Please call Yvonne at (806) 444-8989 since she can give you details about the cats! If you call the Pampa Animal shelter please refer to the cats by their number listed after the names. Thank you for you cooperation!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hello!  My name is Clara and I am about a year old.  I'm a friendly petite kitty.  I will purr up a storm and rub against you until you love and pet me.  I love sitting next to people or on their lap - I'm a lover!   I'm ok with being picked up, held, and carried around.  Don't forget to pet and scratch me - its my favorite.  I absolutely love looking out windows - its my version of tv - so much to see!  I like toys and still have a little "kitten" energy in me!    Don't be surprised if I snuggle up in bed with you!  I am young and have many playful years ahead of me.  I get along with other cats.   I was found as a pregnant stray in the twin cities.  Luckily, I was brought into Twin Cities Pet Rescue and was able to have my four babies in a safe, warm home. I even took on two orphaned kittens - for a total of six.  I was a really good mom, but they are all grown up now and I am ready for a home of my own.

I am spayed, vaccinated for Distemper and Rabies, dewormed, micrcochipped, and Feline and FIV negative.  

Adopt Me: To meet me or learn more about me, please complete an Adoption Application at www.tcpetrescue.org/adopt/adopt-a-cat. If you have general questions about me, you may email cats@tcpetrescue.org.

FOSTER HOMES NEEDED! Twin Cities Pet Rescue is a foster home based organization. We can only rescue as many animals as available homes. If you would like to learn about fostering a cat in need, please e-mail cats@tcpetrescue.org. You may also fill out a Foster Application at http://www.tcpetrescue.org/how-to-foster/foster-a-cat/. TCPR provides all the supplies and veterinary care for your foster animal.
attributes.name: Clara

attributes.descriptionHtml:
I guess you can figure out why my name is Socks! Don’t you think I could have a modeling career? Everyone tells me that I’m very photogenic. As cute as I am, someone dropped me off and left me on a porch. I guess they didn’t want a puppy after all. Now I'm about 7 months old and I love to be cuddled. I was with a foster so I learned some basic commands and manners. But I am a puppy, so occasionally I forget, but I’m extremely smart and I like to learn. I also like to have my belly rubbed .. but who doesn’t. Oh, and I like my ears scratched too. And I love to play non-stop. Chewing on sticks is also one of my favorite past times something about the wood just appeals to me. I love to play fetch with sticks or balls too.

I really need a permanent family to play with. Please give me a chance!

updated 1/3/09 tth

This pet is altered.
This pet is current on vaccinations.
This pet is house-broken

My siblings and I were rescued before being dropped off at the San Bernardino Shelter.  We are eight weeks old and Terrier mixes.  We are all boys and looking for loving homes.
The first step in adopting an animal is to fill out the application. For an application please see our website www.tanyasinc.org and download an application and e-mail it to us.  
All dogs are spayed/neutered, current on vaccinations, dewormed, and are treated with advantix for fleas and ticks. They are also micro chipped(transfer of registration to your name is $20.00).  With every adoption you will also receive a coupons from PETCO.
The best way to get ahold of us is to e-mail Tanya at tanyasinc@msn.com

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Becky...She is part of the "B" litter. She is the sweetest girl, so loving, and gentle. She is good with all her littermates, and loves playing. She has a great nature. She is about 12 weeks old. This is a great litter of easy going puppies, of course they still have all those puppies kisses, and energy! They are up to date on vacc. and monthly preventions. VB 5/14/16

**It is rare that we know with certainty the ages or mixes that make up our wonderful dogs, but we do our best to be as accurate as possible based upon our many years in rescue.**


Adoption: $245  which covers quarantine, shots, worming, food, medical records and an Alabama State Health Certificate.  $35 of this fee is a Spay/Neuter deposit which will be returned to you upon receipt of proof  that the dog has been spayed or neutered.

Transport, if needed :  $120.00    We consider the transport to be of great importance and, as such, take particular care of the dogs during the trip from Alabama. We make every effort to arrive with healthy and minimally stressed dogs.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Rainy is a beautiful brindle dachshund mix! She gets along well with children and other animals. Rainy needs a home that wants a sweet, loving dog that loves to play. Rainy would make a great running or walking companion. She is house-trained, crate-trained, and is a very trainable dog for someone willing to spend the time to train her.

Rainy is spayed and up-to-date with her flea, heartworm, and rabies vaccinations. Rainy does best with limited ingredient dog food. She would make a great addition to a family of any size! Her sweet dachshund expression will melt your heart. She loves to snuggle next to you while you watch your favorite TV show, and runs like a little greyhound when she plays in the backyard.

If you feel your home might be the right place for such a great dog - the place to start is with the adoption application found at www.dfwrescueme.org/adopt. Once submitted, the foster will contact you promptly to tell you more and to arrange a time to meet!

The adoption fee for all of our dogs is $250.00, which includes their vaccinations and spay/neuter.

Rainy is participating in the DFW Rescue Me Guest Dog Program, so ongoing care and custody are provided by their foster, not by DFWRM.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
LILLY and ROSE BUD (aka Mamba Girl) were rescued from a horrible hoarding situation. They are still somewhat shy but have really come out of their shells since living with their foster mom! They both have charming little quirks and are playful, funny and entertaining kitties! Rosebud has become a regular LAP CAT!  She lets you pick her up and cuddle and she loves to be brushed and scratched! She is destined to be your Best Furry Friend!!  Lilly still is not crazy about being picked up, but she loves to be around you and loves to be brushed and scratched just like her sister, especially in the hind quarters. Lilly likes to lay close to you and she trusts humans more and more everyday, now that she sees sister Rosebud is so social and friendly. Lilly and Rose Bud have been through a lot together and would like a forever home together. They will do best in a quiet, mature environment, with a patient, loving family. They will need time to adjust to their new surroundings and learn to trust in their own time frame. Lilly and Rose Bud would LOVE to have a window where they can watch the birds and the squirrels, and they sleep together every night in their big bed. Both girls like dogs and other kitties if appropriately introduced.

Lilly was born approximately February 13, 2012, and Rose Bud was born approximately April 8, 2013, and their combined adoption fee is $82.50. They are both spayed, up to date on shots, vaccinations, flea and parasite treatments, and have tested negative for feline leukemia and FIV. Each is entitled to a free well check at Mariposa Veterinary Wellness Center.

attributes.descriptionHtml: Snow King is a handsome, white, seven month old GSD who was transferred from a shelter where he was surrendered because his former owner was living in a very small place and Snow King had too much energy. According to shelter reports, he had many of the typical puppy behaviors (chewing, house training accidents, jumping on people), but his foster mom has helped him to make significant progress in these areas. He, like all puppies, will need to be properly socialized with both other dogs and people and he would certainly benefit from some basic obedience training so that he'll grow up to be a well balanced adult dog.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Meet Max! Max is a 3 year old healthy neutered male Labrador Retriever mix dog with an incredible story! At 3 months of age, Max was dropped off on my grandmother's front porch… a fluffy but lonely little puppy in need of much love and care. He was left with no note, but only his bed and a food bowl. My sweet grandmother and her husband were known for their love of animals, and so they took the lonely Max into their small family of dogs, raised him, and loved him dearly for the last three years. Sadly, in October of 2015, my grandmother's husband passed away.

Although she has done her best to care for her four dogs, it has proven too difficult. In order to give Max the love, exercise, play, and attention that any young dog deserves, my grandmother has decided that Max would be better off with a new family.

Max is extremely friendly, affectionate, and cuddly. He loves people of all kinds, including children. He is handsome, attentive, goofy, eager to learn, playful and loyal. If you are looking for a dog to take to the park with your kids, to go on runs, to play with your other pets, or just to cuddle, Max is the perfect fit. Max does well with other dogs once he becomes familiar with them (such as the three other dogs in my grandmothers house or my four dogs).

I am currently unsure of his attitude towards cats. Max is neutered, up to date on all vaccines, heartworm negative, and on heartworm and flea prevention. He also had full blood work run recently and all was normal...yay! Max deserves a chance to meet you and finally find his forever home!

If you feel your home might be the right place for such a great dog - the place to start is with the adoption application found at www.dfwrescueme.org/adopt. Once submitted, the foster will contact you promptly to tell you more and to arrange a time to meet!

The adoption fee for all of our dogs is $250.00, which includes their vaccinations and spay/neuter.

Max is participating in the DFW Rescue Me Guest Dog Program, so ongoing care and custody are provided by their foster, not by DFWRM.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Niah is a female Domestic Short Hair silver tabby who was born around August 1st, 2008. Niah may look like a tabby, but inside she is all Siamese. Though she is not overly talkative, this little girl is already the queen of the flock, and needs to have everything just her way. Niah loves to play with toys and foster siblings, but she’ll settle for anything that moves. She has also adopted two adult foster siblings as her parents, and will spend hours snuggled into their long fur getting some quality love. Niah is also happy to cuddle on her humans, and is a huge fan of warm laps on cool nights. Niah cuddles both in and out of the covers, but watch where you sit, because this little girl will burrow her way into a balled up blanket to nap, and could easily get herself squished! Niah is not a big fan of being held, though her foster home has been working on this with treats, and will squirm like crazy unless she has been napping. Niah would love to have a young playmate or someone who can spend lots of time working off her kitten energy, and is ready to find a home to make her own!


ID: Niah

Internal ID: CJP



Thank you for your interest. If you have questions, please contact Kim at cats@yolospca.org, Feline Coordinator.
If you are interested in adopting please follow the instructions below to expedite your application, thank you. cats@yolospca.org
1. Return to our website, www.yolospca.org
2. Download and print out an application, fill it out
3. Fax it to the Feline Coordinator 530 231 2969
4. Please specify which animal you are requesting on the application by noting the "NAME" of the animal and the Internal ID "Code" (3 letters or 3 letters plus 1-digit). Please do not send the "BIO" sheets.
5. We will contact you when we are ready or need more information. Since we get many applications and are volunteers, we may not call you. We only call if we want to further meet with you and feel you may be a match for one of our foster animals. Please e-mail if you have additional questions.





All of our felines have been altered prior to adoption. Kittens have been given their first shots of FVRCP, Feline Leukemia tested (negative), and adults are up to date, and all cats are micro chipped. The fee to adopt is $90 (the fee covers these costs).


The Yolo County SPCA is a private, not-for-profit animal rescue organization. All of our animals awaiting adoption are in foster homes. For more information about this animal please contact the foster home directly at the number, if provided. For more general questions please see our website at www.yolospca.org or contact us through Kim at cats@yolospca.org . If you are reading this, it means that we are still accepting applications, we do remove the pets from our site when they are adopted. We do not have a shelter for you to visit because we are a foster based organization.

Tiger Lily is a very friendly, affectionate orange-and-white girl. She is about 4-1/2 months old now, so is the perfect age to go to a new home. She was rescued by someone who saw her being chased by mean dogs. Despite her traumatic experience, she is outgoing, happy, and loving. She seems to adapt well to new situations, and likes everyone. Tiger Lily loves to play, and to snuggle. If you are looking for a good companion for the upcoming winter, please consider sweet little Tiger Lily.

The adoption fee for this cat is $75, which includes her spaying, as well as her vaccinations (distemper/FVRCP, and feline leukemia). She needs an indoor-only home.

If you would like to see Tiger Lily, please come by the Logan PETsMart and say hello! Or, call Sheri at 435-787-1751 to learn more about meeting or adopting this friendly, loving cat. And thank you for your interest in helping a homeless pet.

attributes.descriptionHtml: This handsome little guy is an absolute doll. At 9 months and 8 lbs, he’s a well-adjusted puppy with lots of Rattie personality. Although he came to New Rattitude with the name Fritz, his high jump has earned him the nickname Jumpin’ Jack Flash, or Jack for short. His favorite things to do, in order, are: snuggle with Foster Mom, eat, play with his canine foster siblings, play in the yard, snuggle with Foster Mom, eat, go for a walk, play with his toys, snuggle with Foster Mom, and sleep in the big bed with everyone...and snuggling with Foster Mom, of course. In spite of a lot of changes in his young life, Fritz is a happy, well-behaved boy with the energy of a puppy out to explore his world. He’s a quick study, who has learned to sit and stay, and even wait, however briefly, for his food. He loves food! He’s gotten comfortable with leash walking and exploring the neighborhood. He’s learned to potty outside, and he’s almost 100 percent reliable on a schedule. He is even learning to give signals that he wants to go out. He sleeps through the night without any accidents, and as long as his foster mom is in bed, he won’t budge from her side. He is a good traveler and does well in the car on family outings. He is OK in his crate, but seems to have a little separation anxiety if he is left in the crate while his foster mom is out. He’s really glad when she gets home and makes sure she knows it by jumping up and down with joy! Because Jack is so attached to his person, he would probably be fine as an only dog, but he would likely be happiest with another canine sibling to play with. He can’t quite figure out who the cat is, but he barks at her. Since he does love to chase squirrels and birds, he might be better off in a feline-free zone. He’s a little shy of people when he first meets them but warms up quickly, especially if treats are involved (see “eat” in favorite things above). Fritz is looking for his “furever” family and is hoping you’re looking "fur" him! For more pictures of this sweetheart, go to http://imageevent.com/newrattitude/fritz .

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Tessa is a 2 year old female French bulldog.  She is house-trained, rides well in a car and even enjoys trips in a travel trailer.  She has been at the lake and around water, and even on a boat on occasion.  Tessa likes to go jogging and is a very active little girl.  Tessa has a rough start in life, purchased as a possible breeding female for a puppy mill, she ended up chained in a back yard and was covered in fleas and ticks.  She is now healthy but, like many dogs, needs a corn and grain free diet.  Tessa was pretty thin when she was rescued, and we think this is what motivates her to guard food, treats and sources of food and treats.  Even the dishwasher!  Tessa can’t be with other dogs because she will attack to protect what she feels is life or death food or food sources.  But, she’s adorable, and in a home with no other dogs, she’ll be a great pet.  We think that she would be best with older children only as well.  Tessa’s $500 adoption fee is being donated as a medical fundraiser for other dogs in Pet Allies care.  Dogs like Weeble who needed a wheelchair, and Hops who was hit by a car.   Tessa's vaccines are current and she has be spayed and has her micro-chip.  Call 928-537-8009 to make an appointment to meet Tessa.

  A home visit will be part of Tessa's adoption process. To start the adoption process, an online adoption application is available at   http://www.petalliesaz.org/dogadopt.php    

Pet Allies, also known as the home of the Barkin Basement Thrift Store at the corner of White Mountain Road and Fawnbrook in Show Low, finds non-lethal solutions to pet overpopulation by offering low-cost spay/neuter services and placing homeless pets in caring homes.  Pet Allies, a non-profit organization, is funded by donations from the community, sales at the Barkin Basement Thrift Store, grants and adoptions.  In October 2012 Pet Allies also entered into a contract with the City of Show Low to operate the City’s animal control shelter where animals may be seen and adopted.    

To visit animals in foster care, call Pet Allies Clinic to make an appointment.    

Pet Allies Clinic & Barkin Basement Thrift Store:  4050 S White Mountain Road - Show Low AZ   Phone:  928 532-1602    

Show Low Animal Control Shelter Facility:  1181 E Thornton Avenue - Show Low AZ   Phone:  928 537-8009

attributes.descriptionHtml: Rufus was found in a shopping center parking lot. We were so worried that he would be hit by a car so we trapped him and by the next day he was such a love. Rufus loves to play, is so so soft ( like a bunny rabbit, or a soft stuffed animal )and is such a joy to foster.He loves jumping up on your lap and giving you kisses. He will be missed once he gets adopted. He also gets along with other cats very well. Rufus would be perfect for an older child, for he is so gentle the only thing is Rufus is shy at first, so it is so important to give him time to get to know you. Rufus is utd on his distemper shots, wormed, FIV/FELV neg. and is neutered and has his rabies shot. Rufus will be at Petco, Easton, PA this Saturday so come down and see him and all the others. For more info call Donna 908-475-2606 or e-mail donnacat@comcast.net

attributes.descriptionHtml: WHAT A WONDERFUL GIRL CHANEL IS: Chanel was picked up by animal control. She was a wild barn cat that was pregnant. With patients and time I was able to work with her and she actually let me pet her (with a swat here and there). She had 4 beautiful kittens that all got adopted. But also with her kittens she nursed (and saved their lives) 12 other kittens without any mothers. She was absolutely amazing. She just took them as if they were her own. Now its Chanels turn to find a loving home. She is utd on all her shots, wormed, FIV/FELV neg. and is now spayed. She loves to come up to you and get attention (only when she wants it), once in a while she is a little swatty, (so I do not recommend young children with her). All she needs is a nice quiet place (other cats are just fine for her) where she can be treated like a princess. You can pick her up and nuzzle her but then she wants to be put down. But she will jump up next to you for attention and loves to be petted but does not like her tail touched. Chanel is such a wonderful cat, yes, I have spoiled her with love and she will be fine with an understanding owner. For more info contact Donna 908-475-2606 or donnacat@comcast.net

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi, my name is Hank. I was rescued from the south and brought up here to the north. I am staying with a foster family who I really like being with, however, I would love to have a family of my own. My foster mom calls me "handsome" as a nickname and I think she is right! I love to run and play ball and I am lucky because I get to run and play with my foster parent's golden retrievers! Because I am young and have a ton of energy I need a family who has alot of time to take me for walks and play ball with me. My foster mom thinks I want to be a "lap dog' because as soon as she sits down I want to crawl on her lap....I just like being close to people.
If you are looking for an awesome, fun dog, fill out an adoption application and my foster mom will be in touch. Because she loves me so much she said that only approved applicants can come and meet me!
I am hoping that you have room in your home for me!!!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Adoption Pending. You can see more of these beautiful dogs by clicking on Rescue Dogs.


Izzy is 3 years old and in search of a new home because she does not get along with the family's female Golden Reteriver. Female pyrs tend to do best with male dogs as housemates and companions. She is great with children, but needs a home where she is the only dog. She is house trained and does not need to be crated. Izzy is very devoted to her family, but takes a while to warm up to strange adults.

NGPR Pooch Profile

Name: Izzy

Age: 3 years

Color: White

Dew Claws: No

Origin: Owner Surrender

Current Location: Indiana Great Pyrenees Rescue Approved Foster

Medical: Neutered, dewormed, heartworm negative, up-to-date on vaccinations and currently on flea, tick and heartworm preventative.

Housebroken: Yes

Can be Placed With: Men, kids, male dogs (no females) and cats

Fencing: Strong, visible fencing required. Pyrs do not do well with inivisible fencing.

Fees:$300 adoption, volunteer transport available.

About Us: National Great Pyrenees Rescue (NGPR) is not a shelter. We are a not-for-profit, tax-exempt coalition of Pyr rescuers and rescue groups. We save Pyrs and Pyr mixes across the country and place them in approved foster homes to learn how they will interact with your family. Every dog who is fostered or adopted makes room for another Pyr coming out of a kill shelter. NGPR dogs are fostered for a minimum of two weeks or more, spayed or neutered and fully vetted before placement. NGPR will take back any dog who does not succeed in its new home. Many NGPR volunteers are members of the AKC breed club, adhere to their rescue guidelines for purebred Pyrs and apply these standards to the adoption of Pyr mixes as well. Visit www.nationalpyr.org to learn more about us, our mission and our breed.

More Information: Questions? The fastest way to learn more about a dog is to fill out the application form below. If you call or e-mail you are reducing your chances of adopting this animal as we direct our time and energy to first serving those who apply. For more information about our adoption process please visit our adoption information page.

Want to help but can’t adopt now? You can make a tax-exempt donation by visiting our donation page.

This exceptional Great Pyrenees dog has been selected for sponsorship by National Great Pyrenees Rescue (NGPR). We have many Pyrs and Pyr mixes who need homes and not all of them are posted. You can see more of these beautiful dogs by clicking on Rescue Dogs. Please fill out our short APPLICATION FORM and we will get back to you within 48 hours. Thanks.


Love this breed? NGPR now has a Rescue Store where your purchase goes to help our rescue dogs and neediest cases.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Hi my name is Gracie! I was rescued and now live with a foster family. I use to live at the end of a long chain, in an old dog house, no shade, and alone most of the time.
I live with my foster family and I now get to run and play ball, get belly-rubs, and I finally have a chance to enjoy life!!! I am thrilled!
My foster parents think I need a home where someone has time to play with me and give me alot of attention. They also think that a home with older children and no other pets would be perfect. She thinks that would be best since I really haven't had a chance to spend a lot of time with little kids and other animals....most of my time was spent alone.
I am a "cuddle bug" as my foster mom calls me, but I am also a strong girl.
I really love being able to sleep inside and get attention from people, but I would love a family of my own even more!
Since I am in a private home, my mom said that only approved applicants can come and meet me. So if you think that you are the right family for me, please fill out an application and my foster mom will be in touch!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Crystal is an adorably pretty girl. Not only is she beautiful on the outside, she is a real sweetheart on the inside as well. Rescued from a bad situation, she is adjusting quickly to her new life in a foster home where she now lives with lots of canine and feline companions. It didn't take her long to realize that life in a warm, comfortable house is much better than sitting in a backyard at the end of a chain and she is showing her appreciation by being totally non-destructive and she was completely housebroken in less than 2 days.

We were told that she is between 3 and 4 years old but she plays like a puppy - she is keeping several younger dogs on their toes with her boundless energy. The cats eyed her with some reservations at first but she is gentle with them and they got comfortable with her in no time. An active family with older children and a canine brother or sister would be an ideal home for this sweet girl.

For more information please fill out APPLICATION


Our Pets can be seen upon appointment or in person every Saturday.


Please visit our EVENTS PAGE for more information on our time and locations.


Pets listed in TARA's web site are eligible to a two week trial.


Adoption fee varies, usually from $150.00.00 to $250.00.


For more information, please visit our Web Site.


Email T.A.R.A. | T.A.R.A.'s Web Site | On-Line Application

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I'm Wendell, and boy do I love the limelight! I arrived here at Angels of Assisi with nine of my friends. Our moms were dropped at the home of a very nice lady who kept them both safe, happy and healthy until were were all born. With the help of some other great people, all my brothers, sisters and friends were cared for, kept healthy and pampered until we were old enough to start looking for our forever homes. I'm a special boy, and I try to demonstrate it at every opportunity. Check out the rest of my pictures. When that photographer lady came in, I posed and posed and posed! I know what a camera is for, even if my friends are unsure. She couldn't turn around without finding me posed for the next shot! I'm a sweet and charming little man. I knew these photos would be used to help me find that terrific forever home, so I'm not blowing my chances on an unflattering image! If it's working for you, come see me any day between 2:00 and 6:00 pm. I can't wait to meet you!
attributes.descriptionText: Hi, I'm Wendell, and boy do I love the limelight!  I arrived here at Angels of Assisi with nine of my friends.  Our moms were dropped at the home of a very nice lady who kept them both safe, happy and healthy until were were all born.  With the help of some other great people, all my brothers, sisters and friends were cared for, kept healthy and pampered until we were old enough to start looking for our forever homes.  I'm a special boy, and I try to demonstrate it at every opportunity.  Check out the rest of my pictures.  When that photographer lady came in, I posed and posed and posed!  I know what a camera is for, even if my friends are unsure.  She couldn't turn around without finding me posed for the next shot!  I'm a sweet and charming little man.  I knew these photos would be used to help me find that terrific forever home, so I'm not blowing my chances on an unflattering image!  If it's working for you, come see me any day between 2:00 and 6:00 pm.  I can't wait to meet you!
attributes.name: WENDELL

attributes.descriptionHtml: Hi, I'm Inka! I arrived here at Angels of Assisi with nine of my friends in October, 2008.  Cinnamon and I are still here from that original group and we think that's a long time without a loving forever home.  We just can't understand why we're still here but maybe it's because we haven't had the opportunity to market ourselves correctly. But I know if you just came and spent a little time with me or Cinnamon you'd see what awesome kitties we are.  Come see us any day between 2:00 and 6:00 pm and we'll show you how wonderful we are.  Love ya, Inka

Thank you for your interest. PLEASE READ THE ENTIRE PAGE BEFORE CALLING OR EMAILING. If you have questions, please e-mail (dogs@yolospca.org).
If you want to adopt please read the following to expedite your application.
1. Return to our website at http://www.yolospca.org
2. Download an application and fill it out. http://www.yolospca.org
3. Fax the application to 530-231-2969, please include the "NAME" of the pet you are interested in on the application.
4. WE will contact you when we are ready or need more info. Since we get many applications and are volunteers, we may not call you. We only call if we want to further meet with you, need more information, and feel the animal may be a good match for your family. Please e-mail if you have additional questions.
All of our canines are altered (spayed & neutered), puppies are started on their shots, adults are up to date and have been heart worm tested (negative) and all dogs are micro chipped. The adoption fee is $175 (which covers all of these costs). THERE IS NO SHELTER FOR YOU TO VISIT BECAUSES WE ARE A FOSTER BASED ORGANIZATION. IF YOU ARE READING THIS THEN WE ARE STILL ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS, WE DO REMOVE THE PETS FROM OUR SITE WHEN THEY HAVE BEEN ADOPTED.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Donovan was found on a rescue mission to save kittens from a roof whose brother had already fallen. Donovan was watching over the kittens and we ended up trapping Donovan, thinking he was mama cat, and three more kittens!

Donovan was spotted watching over the remaining kittens, contentedly, on a rooftop over on Parrish st in West Philly. We quickly realized he was a friendly guy, and particularly so having such a strong maternal instinct, caring for the kittens whose mother was no where to be found. Donovan absolutely adores head rubs and won't let you stop once you start- you've been warned!

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Sweet Cody is a love pup! He is sweet, loving, playful, active and will give the gentlest kisses ! 

Almost hard to believe he is between 6 and 7 years young!

Loves to take slow walks, knows sit and down,  will fetch the ball and bring it back, and hang with you on the couch watching TV.. 

From Codys foster....

""Walk on leash is just perfect; walked yesterday and this morning.  Put him in the crate next to my bed, and just one whimper, that’s all.  Was really well behaved during the bath last night.  No fidgeting.  A total lovebug on the couch with me last night.  Ate well, no issues with the cat.  He was probably fed from the table in his former home, but he isn’t a nuisance about it.  Some itching, some biting of his right paw last night.  But all in all, he’s a treasure and a delight! 

He is lying quietly behind my chair as we speak.

Great dog ""

Interested in meeting him? 

To complete an online application, please click here, then email Randi at rmartin@petconnectrescue.org. 

Adoption procedures, fees, and applications may be viewed by clicking here.

To learn more about the breed(s) of this dog, please go to your favorite search engine and type the breed(s) and "rescue."

The dog adoption fee is $81 for residents of Thurston County that live in Olympia, Lacey or Tumwater City Limits, or $77 for those in unincorporated Thurston County or out of Thurston County Residents. They come spayed/neutered, microchipped, first set of vaccines including DHPP (parvo combo), Bordatella (kennel cough) and Strongid (wormer).

The animals are placed on the webpage by volunteers and are not always current.  If you'd like to check on the status of an animal, please call the shelter at 360-352-2510.  This is especially important if you are viewing this animal on any site other than Animal Services' website.  The staff will need the animal's number (we have it listed as the name) in order to look up the animal.

“Adoption Pending” means someone is in the process of adopting this pet, but has not yet completed the requirements.  Please check back later to see if the animal is available, as we cannot accept reserve applications.

This absolutely precious little boy came to us as a stray so we estimate his age to be 5 yrs. old & he weighs just 12.7 little pounds!  He is super sweet, turns inside out to please you…just precious!  

He is up to date on shots, de-wormed, gets along well w/his kennel mates and he will be neutered prior to his adoption.

96821 / R204078

If you have any questions about this pet please email us at ramonahumanesociety@yahoo.com and we will email you back A.S.A.P. 

Some animals may be taken to Hemet Petsmart on Thurs., Fri., Sat., Sun. for adoption clinic.  Call the front office to ask about a particular animal - 951-654-8002 dial 4 for operator.

To view more wonderful dogs and kitties waiting for you at the Ramona Humane Society, go to petfinder.com/ or AdoptaPet.com and enter the zip code 92582 (San Jacinto, CA.) Please note that we only have a fraction of our dogs and kitties featured on petfinder. Our best advise would be for you to visit our shelter, we have over 300 dogs on any given day waiting to be adopted. Also visit the RHS website at www.ramonahumanesociety.org.  Thank you for thinking about saving a precious life!

Please email ramonahumanesociety@yahoo.com if you have any questions regarding a pet you see on Petfinder or AdoptaPet. Include the pet's reference control number and a volunteer will return your email A.S.A.P.

If you are interested in this pet, please act quickly. Time is of the essence for them.  The Ramona Humane Society Petfinder website is maintained by volunteers only.

ADOPTION HOURS ARE 10 a.m. to 4 p.m. everyday except on Fridays and Sundays the kennels close at 3 p.m.

Office hours are 8 a.m. to 5 p.m. everyday except on Fridays and Sundays...office close at 3 p.m.

SPECIALS:

 If you adopt a dog or cat, the second one is half off!!!

 Seniors 65 yrs. young or older - all adoptions are 1/2 price, regardless of breed, age, etc. No other discounts apply. Senior-to-Senior adoptions - if the dog or cat is 7+ yrs. and already was spayed or neutered prior to entering the facility and the adopter is 65 yrs. young or older, we are now asking for a minimum donation of $25.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Jingles got a terrific home and did not have to be in a store for very long, which was really great!  We wish her and her new owner all the best!

Jingles is a gorgeous girl. She was rescued by A.R.F. after her owner who was suffering from Alzheimer's could no longer care for her.  Jingles lived in a home with another cat and is great with cats, and was ok with the large friendly dog she was fostered with also.  She is a little shy, but such a sweet girl.  Jingles even likes to be cradled and held like a baby! She would love nothing more than a new family to come along and love her forever.  Her foster mom said that Jingles is a very sweet, calm cat, who does not have a mean bone in her body. She's a little love bug! 

Please visit Jingles at the PetSmart in Delray Beach east of I-95 on the south side of Linton Blvd. or apply on-line, and an adoption counselor will get back to you as soon as possible.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
This is Yara a brown tabby female kitten.  She is a Loving Care cat rescue kitty living at All About the Kitties satellite which is located in Spring Grove Pa, for the FASTEST response call 225-5095 or email allaboutthekitties@gmail.com .   You may also visit our site at http://www.allaboutthekitties.org/   We have very flexible hours, you can visit 7 days a week almost any time. 

Yara came with a mom and 3 siblings, soon after their arrival mom and little baby Yazhu became ill, after a visit at an animal  ER it was determined that they had Panleukopenia, we lost both of them.  It’s very rare to be able to save kittens exposed or diagnosed with this disease but when signs starting showing that the other babies were infected they were taken to the ER right away.  Yara and her siblings spent a good while there getting meds, syringe feeding, IV fluids and lots of love.  The end on this story as you can tell is a good one, Yara and her other two siblings pulled through.  They are fighters and good eaters, love playing and now ready for adoption.  She may be adopted but can’t go home until she is 2 lb. and spayed.

Her ID # is KC 267; the adoption fee is $75.00 which includes a negative Felv and FIV test, distemper shots, worm meds and flea treatment plus her spay.  We also offer a microchip for only $25.00 more.   If you choose to adopt 2 Loving Care kitties the fee is only $130.00, two kitties are always better than one.  We cannot hold kittens, its first come first pick.

Thank you for looking

Loving Care cat rescue is an organization that helps cats in need, there are foster homes throughout south central  Pa helping unwanted cats and kittens find new forever homes.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
Say hello to Yoshiko a red tabby female kitten.  She is a Loving Care cat rescue kitty living at All About the Kitties satellite which is located in Spring Grove Pa, for the FASTEST response call 225-5095 or email allaboutthekitties@gmail.com .   You may also visit our site at http://www.allaboutthekitties.org/   We have very flexible hours, you can visit 7 days a week almost any time. 

Yoshiko came with a mom and 3 siblings, soon after their arrival mom and little baby Yazhu became ill, after a visit at an animal  ER it was determined that they had Panleukopenia, we lost both of them.  It’s very rare to be able to save kittens exposed or diagnosed with this disease but when signs starting showing that the other babies were infected they were taken to the ER right away.  Yoshiko and her siblings spent a good while there getting meds, syringe feeding, IV fluids and lots of love.  The end on this story as you can tell is a good one, Yoshiko and her other two siblings pulled through.  They are fighters and good eaters, love playing and now ready for adoption.  She may be adopted but can’t go home until she is 2 lb. and spayed.

Her ID # is KC 265; the adoption fee is $75.00 which includes a negative Felv and FIV test, distemper shots, worm meds and flea treatment plus her spay.  We also offer a microchip for only $25.00 more.   If you choose to adopt 2 Loving Care kitties the fee is only $130.00, two kitties are always better than one.  We cannot hold kittens, its first come first pick.

Thank you for looking

Loving Care cat rescue is an organization that helps cats in need, there are foster homes throughout south central  Pa helping unwanted cats and kittens find new forever homes.

attributes.descriptionHtml:
He's a handful of love, but you have to play, play, play him because he's the cutest thing on four furry paws when he plays, and he's full of energy.  Even at the vets being neutered, he couldn’t stay in a cage.  The techs had to get his cuteness out and play with him.
And talk about photogenic.  He’s a little poser when ‘Mom’ gets the camera out.  He loves being the center of attention.
I have had Marshmellow now for about 2 in half years, He is the most loveable cat I have ever had and this hurts my heart to have to give him up, but I am down sizing and where I am moving I am only aloud to take one animal, since I have three I am only taking the oldest cat with me. My dog will be re-homed with my aunt and uncle. I am looking for the perfect home for Marshmellow.  He loves attention and loves to get treats everyday at 5:30 when I get home. He love his play rats, and loves to cuddle.  I believe he would be perfect for someone with young children that can play with him on a daily basis or with someone that can love on him everyday.
